Jim Varilek
Vice President 
Purchasing and Dow Services Business






J. A. (Jim) Varilek is Vice President of Purchasing for The Dow Chemical Company and Vice President of the Dow Services Business (DSB).  In the Procurement role, Varilek leads the Company’s global Purchasing organization, overseeing purchasing operations and sourcing strategies.  As Vice President of the DSB, Varilek leads the business that is focused on channeling Dow services to joint ventures and non-affiliated companies to accelerate Dow’s strategy implementation.  Varilek also serves as CEO and President of Union Carbide Corporation (UCC).
Varilek joined Dow in August 1982 in Marketing and held a variety of assignments within the Polyethylene Business.  In 1994, Varilek was named Global Leader for Value-Based Management, including responsibility for China Business Development.  Varilek was named Global Business Director for the Epoxy Products & Intermediates Business in October 1997 and in January 2002 was named General Manager for the Advanced Electronic Materials Business.  In February 2004, he was named Business Director for the Chlorinated Organics Business.  Varilek was named Vice President of Global Supply Chain in February 2006 and Vice President for Business Services, Advanced Materials Division in November 2008.  He assumed his current responsibilities as Business Vice President for the Dow Services Business in December 2010 and Vice President of Procurement in July 2013.
Varilek lives in Midland, Michigan and is married with four children, three sons and one daughter.  He is currently the management sponsor of the Disability Employee Network for The Dow Chemical Company, an industry advisory board member for the University of Michigan Tauber Institute for Global Operations, as well as a board member for Independent Community Living.
Varilek has a Bachelor’s Degree in Economics and Master’s in Business Administration from the University of Michigan.
